#: ../../../doc/en/announce/sprint2016.rst:2
msgid "python testing sprint June 20th-26th 2016"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/sprint2016.rst:7
msgid ""
"The pytest core group is heading towards the biggest sprint in its history, "
"to take place in the black forest town Freiburg in Germany.  As of February "
"2016 we have started a `funding campaign on Indiegogo to cover expenses "
"<http://igg.me/at/pytest-sprint/x/4034848>`_ The page also mentions some "
"preliminary topics:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/sprint2016.rst:14
msgid ""
"improving pytest-xdist test scheduling to take into account fixture setups "
"and explicit user hints."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/sprint2016.rst:17
msgid "provide info on fixture dependencies during --collect-only"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/sprint2016.rst:19
msgid ""
"tying pytest-xdist to tox so that you can do \"py.test -e py34\" to run "
"tests in a particular tox-managed virtualenv.  Also look into making pytest-"
"xdist use tox environments on remote ssh-sides so that remote dependency "
"management becomes easier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/sprint2016.rst:25
msgid "refactoring the fixture system so more people understand it :)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/sprint2016.rst:27
msgid ""
"integrating PyUnit setup methods as autouse fixtures. possibly adding ways "
"to influence ordering of same-scoped fixtures (so you can make a choice of "
"which fixtures come before others)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/announce/sprint2016.rst:32
msgid "fixing bugs and issues from the tracker, really an endless source :)"
msgstr ""

